        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Professional staging produces the strongest result on the majority of inner east Brisbane homes priced above $1 million, particularly for owner-occupier-style properties where buyers respond to aspirational presentation. Living in the property during a campaign works for genuinely tidy households on a tight budget, but the rate of inspection-day disruption is high. Listing vacant rarely produces the best price because empty rooms read as small, scale is hard for buyers to judge, and there are no lifestyle cues for the photography or the open homes to work with. The right answer depends on the property type, price bracket, and how realistically you can hold a presentation standard for four to six weeks."
      }
